\
## 1. Product Description\
\
The product is a **web-based AI-powered resume creation and management platform** designed for individuals applying for jobs in international markets.  \
It allows users to **create, edit, translate, version, and export professional resumes** in multiple formats, with a strong focus on long-term accessibility, legal ownership, and scalability.\
\
The platform is **web-first**, with future expansion planned for mobile applications.  \
All user data is securely stored, enabling users to return at any time and re-download or regenerate their resumes.\
\
---\
\
## 2. Core Value Proposition\
\
- Create professional resumes in minutes\
- Maintain full version history and language variants\
- Translate resumes using AI while preserving structure and meaning\
- Export resumes in high-quality PDF and advanced LaTeX formats\
- Access resumes anytime, from anywhere\
- Built for international job markets (US, Canada, EU)\
\
---\
\
## 3. Target Users\
\
- Job seekers applying internationally\
- Immigrants preparing resumes for Canada / EU / US\
- Freelancers and remote workers\
- Students and early-career professionals\
- Power users requiring LaTeX or academic CV formats\
\
---\
\
## 4. Core Functionality\
\
### 4.1 User Accounts & Access\
- Secure user authentication (Email / OAuth)\
- Personal dashboard with resume history\
- Persistent access to all created resumes\
\
---\
\
### 4.2 Resume Creation & Editing\
- Structured resume editor based on JSON schema\
- Editable sections:\
  - Personal information\
  - Work experience\
  - Education\
  - Skills\
  - Languages\
- Automatic versioning on every save\
- Support for multiple resumes per user\
\
---\
\
### 4.3 Resume Versioning\
- Each edit creates a new resume version\
- Ability to restore or re-export previous versions\
- Clear timeline of changes\
\
---\
\
### 4.4 Multilingual Resumes\
- Separate resumes per language\
- Supported languages (MVP):\
  - English\
  - Russian\
  - French\
- AI-generated translations stored as independent resumes\
\
---\
\
### 4.5 AI-Powered Translation\
- Resume translation using Anthropic API\
- Structured JSON-to-JSON translation\
- Translation modes:\
  - Standard translation\
  - Professional CV translation (HR-optimized)\
- Translation usage tracking per user\
\
---\
\
### 4.6 Resume Preview\
- Live preview synchronized with editor\
- Multiple professionally designed HTML/CSS templates\
- Responsive design for desktop and tablet\
\
---\
\
### 4.7 Export & Downloads\
- Primary export format: PDF\
- Optional export formats:\
  - PNG\
  - LaTeX (advanced users)\
- Server-side rendering for consistent formatting\
- Files stored securely and regenerated on demand\
\
---\
\
## 5. Data Storage & Persistence\
\
### 5.1 Source of Truth\
- Resumes stored as structured JSON in PostgreSQL\
- PDF, PNG, and LaTeX treated as derived assets\
\
### 5.2 Version Storage\
- All resume versions stored permanently\
- Language variants stored independently\
\
### 5.3 File Storage\
- Secure object storage using Amazon S3\
- Private buckets with time-limited signed URLs\
\
---\
\
## 6. Monetization Architecture (Prepared, Hidden)\
\
### 6.1 Subscription Model\
- Free plan (default)\
- Pro plan (future activation)\
\
### 6.2 Monetizable Features\
- AI translations\
- Ad-free experience\
- Premium resume templates\
- Unlimited exports and resumes\
\
### 6.3 Payment Processing\
- Stripe integration (backend only)\
- Subscription lifecycle handled via webhooks\
- Monetization UI hidden behind feature flags\
\
---\
\
## 7. Advertising Strategy (Non-Intrusive)\
\
- Banner-only advertising (no popups or interstitials)\
- Sidebar and footer placements\
- Ads fully disabled by default\
- Ads removed automatically for premium users\
\
---\
\
## 8. Technology Stack\
\
### 8.1 Frontend\
- Next.js (React)\
- Tailwind CSS\
- Server-side rendering for SEO\
- Feature-flag-controlled UI\
\
### 8.2 Backend\
- FastAPI (Python)\
- REST API architecture\
- Background tasks for exports and AI requests\
\
### 8.3 Database\
- PostgreSQL\
- JSONB storage for resume content\
- Versioned relational data model\
\
### 8.4 AI Services\
- Anthropic API for resume translation\
\
### 8.5 Payments\
- Stripe (subscriptions and payments)\
\
### 8.6 Advertising\
- Google Ads (prepared, disabled by default)\
\
### 8.7 File Storage\
- Amazon S3\
- Signed URL access control\
\
---\
\
## 9. Hosting & Deployment\
\
- Backend hosting: Render\
- Frontend hosting: Vercel\
- CI/CD pipelines for automated deployment\
- Environment-based configuration (dev / staging / prod)\
\
---\
\
## 10. Security & Compliance\
\
- Secure authentication and authorization\
- Access control by user ownership\
- Encrypted secrets and environment variables\
- Private file storage with expiring access links\
- GDPR-ready data handling\
\
---\
\
## 11. Legal & Ownership\
\
- Platform owned by an international company\
- All intellectual property assigned to the company\
- Source code, domain, and assets legally protected\
- Terms of Service and Privacy Policy in place\
\
---\
\
## 12. Scalability & Future Expansion\
\
- Mobile applications (React Native)\
- Additional languages\
- AI-powered resume improvement and rewriting\
- ATS compatibility analysis\
- Cover letter generation\
- Team and recruiter features\
\
---\
\
## 13. Product Vision\
\
The platform aims to become a **trusted career document hub**, where users can manage all professional resumes across languages, markets, and years \'97 with full ownership, legal clarity, and AI-assisted quality.\
